{"descriptions":[{"id":1253,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eWhen \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྲིད་\u003c/span\u003e are combined with modal verbs, the main verb must go in the present-future. Using the past form would be incorrect.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྙོག་དྲ་ཡོང་སྲིད་ཀྱི་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;There may be problems (later).\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྨོ་ལགས་ལང་ཐུབ་གྱི་མི་འདུག\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;This grandmother can\u0026rsquo;t get up.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eས་ཁུལ་དེར་འགྲོ་ཐུབ་མ་བྱུང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;I couldn\u0026rsquo;t go to that area.\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn this last sentence, for instance, it would be incorrect to say *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eས་ཁུལ་དེར་ཕྱིན་ཐུབ་མ་བྱུང་།\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe verb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་\u003c/span\u003e is compatible with most non-intentional auxiliaries: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་ཀྱི་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་ཀྱི་ཡོད་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་ཀྱི་ཡོད་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་བྱུང་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་སོང་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་པ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་བཞག་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་ཡོད་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e. It is usually incompatible with the following egophoric auxiliaries *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་ཡོད་\u003c/span\u003e, *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་པ་ཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e, *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུབ་ཀྱི་ཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e. The compatibility of \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྲིད་\u003c/span\u003e with auxiliary verbs is relatively restricted. As a rule, only the forms \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྲིད་ཀྱི་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྲིད་པ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e are encountered.\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:21 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:21 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}